About Equail

Equail is a new environmental company from Houston, USA. We want to change how electronic waste (e-waste) is handled in our area. Our main goal is to collect old and unused electronics by hiring mostly unemployed people. This way, these e-wastes donâ€™t end up in landfills or hurt the environment. We work with top recycling partners in Swedenâ€”a country known for great recycling methods, to make sure every device we collect is used again in a way that helps the Earth. Equail also helps unemployed people by giving them good job opportunities. And Equail can support unemployed people by contributing appropriate job.

At Equail, we care about using technology responsibly, helping people understand the environment, and making sure e-waste gets reused instead of thrown away. We follow a clear process to handle e-waste safely, transport it in ways that are good for the Earth, and recycle it with trusted partners at every step.

Our Process: How Your E-Waste Finds New Life

1. Safe E-Waste Collection

Equail has set up a network of innovative e-waste collection points, designed like vending machines, across Houston and surrounding areas. Additionally, we hire unemployed individuals to act as e-waste collectors, providing them with certain level of job skills and a steady income. Our collectors are trained to identify and type of e-watste, ensuring that every e-waste is collected and transported transparently.

2. Export to Swedish Recycling Partners

Through our exclusive partnerships with certified recyclers in Sweden, your collected electronics are shipped and tracked to their destination. Swedenâ€™s advanced infrastructure and commitment to nearly zero landfill waste ensures each device is recycled efficiently and responsibly.

3. Advanced Recycling and Material Recovery

In Sweden, specialized facilities carefully disassemble, sort, and decontaminate e-waste. Hazardous materials such as batteries, mercury, and heavy metals are separated and disposed of safely, while valuable raw materialsâ€”including metals, plastics, and glassâ€”are reclaimed for reuse in new products.

Our Impact

  • Solving the problem of unemployment by providing jobs for the unemployed through electronic waste collection and recycling.
  • Conservation of the environment by reducing the amount of e-waste thrown away, which helps to mitigate the negative impacts of e-waste on the environment, such as pollution and shortage of resources.
